An Army Officer passed away... <br>
Upon being met at the Pearly Gates, he is asked by St. Peter what is his most hearfelt desire. &quot;To NEVER be around any Marines!&quot; was his emphatic response. <br>
St. Peter assured him that Marines only guard the gates and that they were not allowed into the officers lounge.<br>
A few weeks later, while relaxing in the Angel's lounge who should walk in but a Marine in dress blues, with all his medals. Furious, the officer marches off to find St. Peter to complain. <br>
St. Peter calms the man by saying, &quot;There are no Marines in the officer's lounge. That was God... he just likes to pretend that he's one.&quot; <br><br>

